INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('After walking around the house, you become aware of fine bits of a stange metal stuck to your clothes. You can feel the metallic dust emanating a strange energy. Gain 1 Clue token and then make a Luck (-1) check. If you fail, a monster appears.','Luck -1','Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Approaching the house, you notice three youngs boys crouching in the bushes by the side of the drive. Questioning them, you get nothing but variations on the rumors you''ve heard in town: One boy insists the place is haunted, while the other two maintain that Mrs. Gardner is a witch. However, just as you''re about to give up in despair, one of them lets slip a detail of great importance to you. Gain 2 Clue tokens.',NULL,'Dunwich Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Emaciated cattle wander through the area, their hide turned grey by some unknown force. Make a Lore (-1) check. If you pass, gain 1 Clue token as you gain useful knowledge by studying these strangely afflicted creatures.','Lore -1','Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Erica Carlyle is investigating the stories of the mysterious stone that fell from the heavens, and her interest is piqued by your tales of the bizarre. If you have $3 or less, she agrees to help you and help pay your way. Take her Ally card or, if it is not available, gain a Retainer card.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Inside the Gardners'' house you find strange, erratic writings covering some of the walls. Most of it seems to be nonsense but hidden within the ramblings are some startling revelations. If you choose to investigate thoroughly, gain 3 Clue tokens, and you are delayed.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Make a Luck (-1) check. If you fail, something deep within the well seems to call to you. Pass a Will (-1) check or you leap into the well to be devoured. If you pass either check, nothing happens.','Luck -1
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Night falls, and you witness the vegetation of the area glowing and squirming of its own accord. Lose 1 Sanity.',NULL,'Dunwich Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Strange currents of mystical energy flow through this area. If 2 or more rifts are open, add 1 Dunwich Horror token to the board.',NULL,'Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('The more corrupt Dunwich becomes, the more this area rots the minds of those who encounter it. Make a Will (+2) check. If the number of successes is less than the total number of monster tokens in Dunwich locations and Dunwich street areas, draw a [[Madness] card.','Will +2','Miskatonic Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('Wandering through the house, you peer into the attic. Inside, a filthy woman squats on the floor like an animal and growls viciously at you before leaping to attack. Pass a Speed (-1) check to escape or lose 1 Stamina. In either event, lose 1 Sanity.','Speed -1','Dunwich Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('You are attacked by a hideous bald creature that leaps out of the bushes at you. Make a Luck (-1) check. If you pass, the creature is weak and easily slain. If you fail, its sharp teeth tear into your neck. Lose 2 Stamina. In either event, you lose 1 Sanity as you realize that thise abomination was once an ordinary rabbit.','Luck -1','Dunwich Horror');
INSERT INTO gardners_place_encounters VALUES ('You are filled with an unnatural vigor. Your Stamina is restored to its maximum. In addition, you gain 3 extra Stamina above your maximum that cannot be restored once lost.',NULL,'Dunwich Horror');
